rComments: The course is dry and he doesn't make it any interesting but it's not difficult to get a good grade in this course. Labs are boring, long and tedious but mark depends on TA. For the midterms and exams, just do problems from past tests and exams he posts on the website. Stopped going to the lectures after the first test as they were really useless.

Lectures are only good for concepts and preparing for conceptual questions on tests. It's a bunch of equations without showing how to apply them to solve problems. Youtube videos for solving problems and Tutorials are life savers. Tests and labs are easy. Don't buy the textbook, just find a generic thermodynamics textbook online.
Great prof, really enjoyed the course.

He has a really great sense of humor and seems like a great person but just was not prepared for lectures. He would come to class and read off the slides, sometimes even math based problems. I was really annoyed that there was a mistake in a  question on the exam that made it unsolvable (literally!) and he announced it halfway through the exam :

He is the best chemphysics prof. He explains the stuff very clearly and a really nice person. Great lectures and tests are reasonable if you study enough. If you have decent background in mathematics and physics you should be fine.

He is is one of the best chem professors at utm, explains his concepts very clearly and is also quite entertating. His classes are not that diffcult. You will atleast get 75 if you are an avg student, you might get 85+ if you are really smart !!he is very helpful
He's not always clear. But if you read the lecture notes before class you should be fine. He has the best website with everything!

He has great sense of humour during lectures. He is helpful when you have questions in the lab. He has everything you need through the website (old tests, manuals). He is an excellent professor to have in physical chemistry.

super nice prof... so helpful... give us all the resources we need including forwarding individual questions with his answers to everyone in class... SO nice and so enthusiastic... sucks that class was at 8am otherwise his class would be the only class that i enjoy going to....
